{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875610861,"sessionID":"ses_2859188c7ffe1jYyOXtLUWppts","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6f5462001jIjEGNQJtvur6z","messageID":"msg_d7a6f3ecb001FG1sd2gi5uibUF","sessionID":"ses_2859188c7ffe1jYyOXtLUWppts","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6601f3dab84f47278d45c4e2c7b74c7e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-022 |\n8: | Module | cmd/cli |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: Implement the `publish` command in AgentCube CLI to deploy agent containers to Kubernetes. The command orchestrates the entire publish lifecycle: preparing container images (Docker push or explicit URL), deploying to target infrastructure (AgentCube AgentRuntime CR or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service), and updating metadata with deployment information.\n17: \n18: **Current State**: CLI has `pack` and `build` commands that generate Dockerfile and build container images, but no deployment capability. Users must manually push images and create Kubernetes resources.\n19: \n20: **Target State**: \n21: - Single `kubectl-agentcube publish` command that deploys agents to Kubernetes\n22: - Support for two providers: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service)\n23: - Automatic image preparation via Docker push or explicit image URL\n24: - Metadata updated with deployment info, agent_id, and endpoint URLs\n25: - Namespace, replicas, and NodePort configuration support\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n30: \n31: ### 2.1 In Scope\n32: \n33: | Deliverable | Description |\n34: |-------------|-------------|\n35: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` class with publish orchestration logic |\n36: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | `publish` Typer command with CLI options |\n37: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` for standard K8s Deployment/Service |\n38: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR deployment |\n39: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Image push methods (extends AR-021) |\n40: \n41: ### 2.2 PublishRuntime Methods\n42: \n43: | Method | Purpose |\n44: |--------|---------|\n45: | `publish(workspace_path, **options)` | Main orchestration entry point |\n46: | `_publish_cr_to_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, **options)` | Deploy via AgentCube AgentRuntime CR |\n47: | `_publish_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, **options)` | Deploy via standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service |\n48: | `_prepare_image_for_publishing(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Image preparation (push or URL) |\n49: | `_prepare_local_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Push local Docker image to registry |\n50: | `_prepare_cloud_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Use cloud-built image URL |\n51: | `_update_publish_metadata(workspace_path, agent_info)` | Persist deployment info to metadata YAML |\n52: \n53: ### 2.3 CLI Options\n54: \n55: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n56: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n57: | `--workspace` / `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace directory |\n58: | `--version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) |\n59: | `--image-url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Image repository URL (required in local build mode) |\n60: | `--image-username` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Username for image repository |\n61: | `--image-password` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Password for image repository |\n62: | `--description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n63: | `--region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n64: | `--cloud-provider` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n65: | `--provider` | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n66: | `--node-port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Specific NodePort (30000-32767) for K8s |\n67: | `--replicas` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Number of replicas (default: 1) |\n68: | `--namespace` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Kubernetes namespace |\n69: | `--verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n70: \n71: ### 2.4 Out of Scope\n72: \n73: | Item | Reason |\n74: |------|--------|\n75: | Cloud publish implementation | Requires cloud provider SDK integration; placeholder only |\n76: | Helm chart deployment | Different deployment paradigm; future enhancement |\n77: | Auto-scaling configuration | Not specified in requirements; HPA would be separate feature |\n78: | Secret management | Beyond current scope; requires vault integration |\n79: | Multi-cluster deployment | Requires federation setup; future enhancement |\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n84: \n85: ### 3.1 新增文件\n86: \n87: ```\n88: cmd/cli/\n89: ├── agentcube/\n90: │   ├── runtime/\n91: │   │   └── publish_runtime.py     # PublishRuntime class\n92: │   ├── services/\n93: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py        # KubernetesProvider class\n94: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py  # AgentCubeProvider class\n95: │   │   └── docker_service.py      # (extend with push_image)\n96: │   └── cli/\n97: │       └── main.py                # publish command (addition to existing)\n98: └── tests/\n99:     ├── test_publish_runtime.py    # Unit tests for PublishRuntime\n100:     ├── test_k8s_provider.py       # Unit tests for KubernetesProvider\n101:     └── test_agentcube_provider.py # Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider\n102: ```\n103: \n104: ### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n105: \n106: | Dependency | Version | Impact |\n107: |------------|---------|--------|\n108: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Python client for Kubernetes API; optional dependency under `[k8s]` extras |\n109: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image push operations |\n110: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n111: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and table output |\n112: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n113: | `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future cloud integration |\n114: \n115: ### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n116: \n117: | Consumer | Method Usage |\n118: |----------|--------------|\n119: | `invoke` command | Uses agent_endpoint from metadata for HTTP calls |\n120: | `status` command | Reads k8s_deployment info from metadata |\n121: | `pack`/`build` commands | Provide image info for publish flow |\n122: | Users | CLI invocation `kubectl-agentcube publish -f ./my-agent` |\n123: \n124: ### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n125: \n126: - **Metadata schema**: Adding `k8s_deployment` field with sub-fields (`type`, `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `node_port`, `service_url`, `agent_id`)\n127: - **Provider parameter**: New `--provider` flag changes behavior significantly\n128: - **AgentRuntime CR dependency**: Requires Volcano AgentCube CRD installed for `agentcube` provider\n129: - **Registry credentials**: Password passed via CLI flag (insecure); recommend env vars or secret files\n130: \n131: ### 3.5 Compatibility Notes\n132: \n133: - Kubernetes client `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()` reads from `~/.kube/config` by default\n134: - NodePort range must be 30000-32767 per Kubernetes specification\n135: - AgentRuntime CR uses API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n136: - Image URL format: `{registry}/{repository}/{image}:{tag}`\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n141: \n142: ### Alternative 1: Direct kubectl Execution\n143: \n144: **Approach**: Generate YAML manifests and execute `kubectl apply` via `subprocess.run()`.\n145: \n146: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n147: |--------|------------|\n148: | Pros | Familiar to K8s users; no Python SDK dependency |\n149: | Cons | No programmatic status checks; harder error parsing; platform-specific; no wait-for-ready logic |\n150: \n151: **Decision**: Rejected. Kubernetes Python SDK provides typed API, wait loops, and structured status retrieval.\n152: \n153: ### Alternative 2: Helm Chart Publishing\n154: \n155: **Approach**: Package agent as Helm chart and use `helm install` for deployment.\n156: \n157: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n158: |--------|------------|\n159: | Pros | Standard K8s packaging; templating support; versioning built-in |\n160: | Cons | Requires Helm CLI; additional complexity; not in original spec |\n161: \n162: **Decision**: Rejected for initial scope. May add as alternative publishing mode in future.\n163: \n164: ### Alternative 3: Separate Push and Deploy Commands\n165: \n166: **Approach**: Split into `push-image` and `deploy` commands instead of unified `publish`.\n167: \n168: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n169: |--------|------------|\n170: | Pros | More granular control; can push without deploying |\n171: | Cons | More commands to learn; friction in typical workflow |\n172: \n173: **Decision**: Rejected. Unified `publish` command matches spec requirements and provides smoother user experience.\n174: \n175: ### Alternative 4: Docker Compose for Local Testing\n176: \n177: **Approach**: Support Docker Compose as deployment target for local development.\n178: \n179: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n180: |--------|------------|\n181: | Pros | Easy local testing; no K8s required |\n182: | Cons | Different networking model; not production-ready |\n183: \n184: **Decision**: Rejected. Focus on Kubernetes deployment per spec; local testing via `docker run` sufficient.\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## 5. Risks\n189: \n190: | Risk | Mitigation |\n191: |------|------------|\n192: | Kubernetes cluster unreachable | Load kubeconfig first; fail early with clear error message |\n193: | AgentRuntime CRD not installed | `AgentCubeProvider` checks CR existence; raises `ValueError` if not found |\n194: | Missing router_url/workload_manager_url for agentcube | Validation in `_publish_cr_to_k8s` raises `ValueError` |\n195: | Image push auth failure | `DockerService._docker_login_sdk` handles credentials; log warning on failure |\n196: | Deployment timeout | `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready(timeout=120)` raises `TimeoutError` |\n197: | NodePort collision | K8s auto-assigns if NodePort not specified; validation for range 30000-32767 |\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n202: \n203: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.__init__()` with namespace, kubeconfig options\n204: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._ensure_namespace()` to create namespace if missing\n205: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` for Deployment + Service creation\n206: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._create_deployment()` with sanitization, env_vars\n207: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._create_service()` with NodePort handling\n208: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready()` with timeout loop\n209: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()` for pod/deployment status\n210: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent()` for cleanup\n211: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._sanitize_name()` for K8s name compliance\n212: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.__init__()` with namespace, kubeconfig options\n213: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider._ensure_namespace()` \n214: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` for AgentRuntime CR\n215: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider._sanitize_name()` for CR name compliance\n216: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime()` for CR status retrieval\n217: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime.publish()` orchestration entry point\n218: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()` for AgentCube provider\n219: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s()` for standard K8s provider\n220: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing()` image preparation\n221: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()` Docker push logic\n222: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_cloud_image()` cloud image URL handling\n223: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata()` metadata persistence\n224: - [ ] Add `publish` Typer command in `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n225: - [ ] Add error handling with `_handle_error()` for verbose traceback\n226: - [ ] Add Rich `Progress` spinner for publish status\n227: - [ ] Add `k8s_deployment` and `agent_id` fields to `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n228: - [ ] Unit tests for KubernetesProvider mock K8s API\n229: - [ ] Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider mock CR API\n230: - [ ] Unit tests for image preparation logic\n231: - [ ] Integration test for full publish workflow (mocked)\n232: \n233: ---\n234: \n235: ## 7. References\n236: \n237: - Spec: `changes/AR-022/spec.md`\n238: - Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n239: - CLI Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Requirement: `publish` command\n240: - Deployment Spec: `deployment/spec.md` — Kubernetes deployment patterns\n241: - Python SDK Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md` — AgentRuntimeClient integration\n242: - AR-021 — CLI build command (image preparation dependency)\n243: - Kubernetes Python Client: https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python\n244: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n245: - Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n\n(End of file - total 245 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-022 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | L |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nImplement the `publish` command in AgentCube CLI to deploy agent containers to Kubernetes. The command orchestrates the entire publish lifecycle: preparing container images (Docker push or explicit URL), deploying to target infrastructure (AgentCube AgentRuntime CR or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service), and updating metadata with deployment information.\n\n**Current State**: CLI has `pack` and `build` commands that generate Dockerfile and build container images, but no deployment capability. Users must manually push images and create Kubernetes resources.\n\n**Target State**: ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775875610836,"end":1775875610858}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775875610888,"sessionID":"ses_2859188c7ffe1jYyOXtLUWppts","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6f58ec001IZoypyPYeDU93g","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a6f3ecb001FG1sd2gi5uibUF","sessionID":"ses_2859188c7ffe1jYyOXtLUWppts","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":48427,"input":1089,"output":171,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":47167}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775875613971,"sessionID":"ses_2859188c7ffe1jYyOXtLUWppts","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6f6510001LAV5VWSD2E9XVc","messageID":"msg_d7a6f591f00148Ym4Zgzipluus","sessionID":"ses_2859188c7ffe1jYyOXtLUWppts","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875615326,"sessionID":"ses_2859188c7ffe1jYyOXtLUWppts","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6f6a2a001Jk45nSwycBCReR","messageID":"msg_d7a6f591f00148Ym4Zgzipluus","sessionID":"ses_2859188c7ffe1jYyOXtLUWppts","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c27c21870a1946289160ce7df64862e5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Command-line tool (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Global CLI options\n10: The system SHALL expose a Typer application named `agentcube` with global options on the root callback.\n11: \n12: #### Scenario: Version display\n13: - **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n14: - **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n15: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n16: \n17: #### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n18: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n19: - **WHEN** the callback runs\n20: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n21: \n22: ### Requirement: `pack` command\n23: The system SHALL provide `pack` to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a `Dockerfile`, and report paths.\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n26: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack`\n27: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n28: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`); `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`); `language` = `None` (`--language`); `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`); `port` = `None` (`--port`, `Optional[int]`); `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`); `description` = `None` (`--description`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, command-local)\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Successful pack\n31: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n32: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n33: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` (reported as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`), using a Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Pack failure handling\n36: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises\n37: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n38: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code `1`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: `build` command\n41: The system SHALL build a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default in metadata), with optional proxy and tag derived from metadata version.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n44: - **GIVEN** the user runs `build`\n45: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n46: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`); `proxy` = `None` (`-p` / `--proxy`); `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`)\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Local Docker build prerequisites\n49: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n50: - **WHEN** Docker is unavailable\n51: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` surfaced via CLI error handling\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Version increment on build\n54: - **GIVEN** a successful local build path\n55: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs\n56: - **THEN** the system SHALL increment `metadata.version` (patch bump for `X.Y.Z`, or append `.1` / fallback `{version}-1`) before build and revert the version in metadata if build fails\n57: \n58: ### Requirement: `publish` command\n59: The system SHALL publish/deploy using provider `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service), preparing the image via Docker push or explicit image URL as implemented in `PublishRuntime`.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n62: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish`\n63: - **THEN** defaults SHALL include: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `version` = `None` (`--version`); `image_url` = `None` (`--image-url`); `image_username` = `None` (`--image-username`); `image_password` = `None` (`--image-password`); `description` = `None`; `region` = `None` (`--region`); `cloud_provider` = `None`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`); `node_port` = `None` (`--node-port`, `Optional[int]`); `replicas` = `None` (`--replicas`); `namespace` = `None` (`--namespace`); `verbose` = `False`\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider prerequisites\n66: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n67: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n68: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Standard Kubernetes publish flow\n71: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes client initializes\n72: - **WHEN** publish proceeds\n73: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`, then `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`, updating metadata with deployment info; on readiness failure it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` after recording error in metadata\n74: \n75: ### Requirement: `invoke` command\n76: The system SHALL POST JSON to the published agent endpoint, parse `--payload` as JSON, merge optional `--header` entries, and for AgentRuntime CR deployments rewrite the URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n79: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke`\n80: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `payload` = `\"{}\"` (`--payload`, `str`); `header_list` = `None` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`); `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Invalid payload\n83: - **GIVEN** `payload` is not valid JSON\n84: - **WHEN** the command parses it\n85: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print invalid JSON in red and exit with code `1` (before `_handle_error`)\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Invalid header format\n88: - **GIVEN** a header string without a single `:` separator\n89: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n90: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print expected `key:value` format and exit with code `1`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Session header on invoke\n93: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id`\n94: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n95: - **THEN** the HTTP client SHALL add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (same spelling as response handling) to the request\n96: \n97: ### Requirement: `status` command\n98: The system SHALL load workspace metadata and display agent status in a Rich `Table`, exiting with code `1` when status is `not_published` or `error`.\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n101: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status`\n102: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: Not published\n105: - **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id`\n106: - **WHEN** `get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n107: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print guidance to publish first and exit with code `1`\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Workspace validation (pack path)\n110: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and is a directory; for Python, require at least one `*.py` file; for Java, require `pom.xml`.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Missing workspace\n113: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` does not exist\n114: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n115: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message that the directory does not exist\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Python workspace without Python files\n118: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n119: - **WHEN** no `*.py` exists in the workspace root\n120: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n121: \n122: ### Requirement: Metadata file format\n123: The system SHALL persist agent configuration as YAML. The primary filename SHALL be `agent_metadata.yaml`; loading SHALL fall back to `agent.yaml` then `metadata.yaml` if the primary file is missing.\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Save location\n126: - **GIVEN** metadata is saved\n127: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n128: - **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, excluding `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Schema validation\n131: - **GIVEN** YAML is loaded\n132: - **WHEN** fields violate `AgentMetadata` validators\n133: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject unsupported `language` / `build_mode` or invalid `port` range\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: Docker integration\n136: The system SHALL use the Docker SDK (`docker.from_env()`) to build images, push to a registry when configured, and optionally remove images.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Build image\n139: - **GIVEN** Docker is running\n140: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n141: - **THEN** it SHALL tag `{image_name}:{tag}`, pass optional `buildargs` from proxy settings, and return `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Push image\n144: - **GIVEN** a local image name and optional `registry_url` / credentials\n145: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image` runs\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL login if username and password are provided, retag when needed, stream push logs, and return `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Remove image\n149: - **GIVEN** `DockerService.remove_image(image_name)` is called\n150: - **WHEN** removal succeeds\n151: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True`; on failure it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n152: \n153: ### Requirement: Kubernetes — standard provider\n154: The system SHALL create or patch `Deployment` and `NodePort` `Service`, wait for rollout, report pod status, and support deletion.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Deploy agent\n157: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n158: - **WHEN** resources are applied\n159: - **THEN** the result SHALL include `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Wait for ready\n162: - **GIVEN** a deployment name\n163: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds `timeout` seconds (default `120`)\n164: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `TimeoutError`\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: Delete agent\n167: - **GIVEN** `delete_agent` is called\n168: - **WHEN** deletion completes\n169: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}` ignoring 404 on individual deletes\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: Kubernetes — AgentCube AgentRuntime CR\n172: The system SHALL create or patch an `AgentRuntime` custom object in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, plural `agentruntimes`.\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Deploy CR\n175: - **GIVEN** required readiness probe fields exist in metadata\n176: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` runs\n177: - **THEN** it SHALL embed `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL` from parameters or environment when missing in `env_vars`, set `sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`, and reference `imagePullSecrets` `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n178: \n179: ### Requirement: AgentCube provider integration (CLI)\n180: The system SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` for `provider=agentcube` publish/status flows and `KubernetesProvider` for `provider=k8s`.\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Status for AgentRuntime\n183: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and the CR exists\n184: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n185: - **THEN** status SHALL be read from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present (`status`, `agentEndpoint`), else `created_no_status`, else `not_found_in_k8s`\n186: \n187: ### Requirement: Error handling patterns\n188: The system SHALL use `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)` for subcommand exceptions: print `Error {command_name}: {e}` in red; if `verbose`, print traceback; raise `typer.Exit(1)`.\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Subcommand verbose vs global verbose\n191: - **GIVEN** a subcommand’s local `--verbose` is `True` but global `-v` was not passed\n192: - **WHEN** an error occurs in that subcommand\n193: - **THEN** traceback SHALL still be printed because `_handle_error` receives the subcommand’s `verbose` flag\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: **Note:** The implementation uses `agent_metadata.yaml` as the canonical metadata filename (with `agent.yaml` / `metadata.yaml` fallbacks for load). Documentation that refers to `agentcube.yaml` SHALL be treated as naming drift unless a separate file is introduced in code.\n\n(End of file - total 197 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nCommand-line tool (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Global CLI options\nThe system SHALL expose a Typer application named `agentcube` with global options on the root callback.\n\n#### Scenario: Version display\n- **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n- **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n\n#### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n- **WHEN** the callback runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md","time":{"start":1775875615305,"end":1775875615322}}}}
