{"type":"text","timestamp":1775875678215,"sessionID":"ses_2859188c7ffe1jYyOXtLUWppts","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6fa8c0001644mhExBwTRLDd","messageID":"msg_d7a6f6a8d001D2pUjd0k2dE2tY","sessionID":"ses_2859188c7ffe1jYyOXtLUWppts","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context needed. Let me write the proposal.md for AR-024:","time":{"start":1775875678211,"end":1775875678211}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875678266,"sessionID":"ses_2859188c7ffe1jYyOXtLUWppts","part":{"id":"prt_d7a706005001akxNpiKkak3BfS","messageID":"msg_d7a6f6a8d001D2pUjd0k2dE2tY","sessionID":"ses_2859188c7ffe1jYyOXtLUWppts","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-c119a61920a14965b01b38a1f7023cc5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md","content":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-024 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nEncapsulate Docker SDK operations into a well-structured `DockerService` class that provides a clean abstraction layer for container image lifecycle management (build, push, remove). This service acts as the foundation for CLI `build` and `publish` commands, enabling:\n\n1. **Docker Availability Check**: Verify Docker daemon connectivity before operations\n2. **Image Building**: Build container images from Dockerfile with proxy support\n3. **Image Information Retrieval**: Get metadata (ID, size) for built images\n4. **Image Pushing**: Push images to registries with authentication support\n5. **Image Removal**: Clean up local images after operations\n\n**Current State**: Basic `DockerService` exists with core methods (`build_image`, `push_image`, `remove_image`, `get_image_info`, `check_docker_available`), but lacks proper SDK-based helper methods (`_docker_login_sdk`, `_tag_image_sdk`) and has incomplete `_get_image_info` implementation. The class uses inline Docker client calls instead of proper encapsulation.\n\n**Target State**: \n- Complete `DockerService` with all methods per design specification\n- Add `_docker_login_sdk()` for SDK-based registry authentication\n- Add `_tag_image_sdk()` for SDK-based image tagging\n- Add `_get_image_info()` as internal implementation detail\n- Consistent error handling with verbose logging\n- Full unit test coverage with mocked Docker SDK\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope (范围)\n\n### 2.1 In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Complete `DockerService` class with all public and private methods |\n| `tests/test_docker_service.py` | Unit tests for all `DockerService` methods |\n\n### 2.2 DockerService Methods\n\n| Method | Purpose | Status |\n|--------|---------|--------|\n| `__init__(verbose)` | Initialize service with verbose flag | Existing |\n| `check_docker_available()` | Ping Docker daemon to verify availability | Existing |\n| `build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag, build_args)` | Build image from Dockerfile, return image metadata | Existing |\n| `get_image_info(image_name)` | Get image ID and size for a given image | Existing |\n| `_get_image_info(image_name)` | Internal implementation for image info retrieval | To Add |\n| `_format_size(size_bytes)` | Convert bytes to human-readable size string | Existing |\n| `push_image(image_name, registry_url, username, password)` | Push image to registry with optional auth | Existing |\n| `_docker_login_sdk(registry, username, password)` | SDK-based Docker registry login | To Add |\n| `_tag_image_sdk(source_image, target_image)` | SDK-based image tagging for push | To Add |\n| `remove_image(image_name)` | Remove local image, return success boolean | Existing |\n\n### 2.3 Out of Scope\n\n| Item | Reason |\n|------|--------|\n| Docker daemon installation/setup | Assumes Docker is already installed on the host |\n| Container runtime operations | Only image lifecycle, not container execution |\n| Multi-platform image builds | Not specified in requirements; `docker buildx` would be separate feature |\n| Docker Compose integration | Different paradigm; CLI uses `build` + `publish` workflow |\n| Cloud provider Docker APIs | Cloud build mode is handled by `BuildRuntime._build_cloud` |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n\n### 3.1 新增文件\n\nNo new files; modifications to existing files:\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├ agentcube/\n│   └── services/\n│       └── docker_service.py       # MODIFY: Add _docker_login_sdk, _tag_image_sdk, _get_image_info\n└── tests/\n    └── test_docker_service.py      # MODIFY: Add tests for new methods\n```\n\n### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Impact |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python; `docker.from_env()` for client initialization |\n| `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | `AgentMetadata` type in `build_image_legacy` |\n| Standard library `time` | N/A | Build/push timing measurement |\n\n### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Method Usage |\n|----------|--------------|\n| `BuildRuntime._build_local` | `check_docker_available()`, `build_image()`, `get_image_info()` |\n| `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image` | `push_image()`, `_docker_login_sdk()`, `_tag_image_sdk()` |\n| `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing` | `push_image()` |\n| `tests/test_build_runtime.py` | Mock `DockerService` methods |\n| `tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | Mock `DockerService` methods |\n\n### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n\n- **No breaking changes**: All public method signatures remain unchanged\n- **New private methods**: `_docker_login_sdk`, `_tag_image_sdk`, `_get_image_info` are internal; no API impact\n- **Behavioral change**: `push_image` may now use `_tag_image_sdk` for explicit tagging before push\n\n---\n\n## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n\n### Alternative 1: subprocess-based Docker CLI\n\n**Approach**: Use `subprocess.run()` to execute `docker build`, `docker push`, `docker tag` commands.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | No SDK dependency; familiar CLI commands; easier debugging |\n| Cons | Platform-specific path handling; harder error parsing; no structured output; no streaming logs via SDK |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Docker SDK (`docker.from_env()`) provides structured API responses, proper error types, and consistent behavior across platforms.\n\n### Alternative 2: Docker API REST client\n\n**Approach**: Use `httpx` to call Docker Engine REST API directly (`/build`, `/images/push`).\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | No SDK dependency; flexible request handling |\n| Cons | Requires Docker socket access; complex auth header handling; less robust than SDK |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Docker SDK already handles socket communication, TLS, and authentication correctly.\n\n### Alternative 3: Separate ImageService and RegistryService\n\n**Approach**: Split Docker operations into `ImageService` (build, remove) and `RegistryService` (login, push, tag).\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Smaller classes; clearer separation |\n| Cons | More complexity; image lifecycle is cohesive; spec defines single `DockerService` |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. All Docker operations are cohesive for CLI workflow; single class matches design specification.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Docker daemon not running | `check_docker_available()` ping before operations; fail fast with `RuntimeError` |\n| Registry authentication failure | `_docker_login_sdk()` catches exceptions; verbose logging |\n| Image tag mismatch | `_tag_image_sdk()` validates source/target; logs on failure |\n| Build timeout | No explicit timeout in SDK; CLI level timeout in `BuildRuntime` |\n| Large image sizes | `_format_size()` handles GB ranges; no truncation |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Add `_docker_login_sdk(self, registry, username, password)` method\n- [ ] Add `_tag_image_sdk(self, source_image, target_image)` method\n- [ ] Add `_get_image_info(self, image_name)` private implementation\n- [ ] Update `push_image` to use `_docker_login_sdk` and `_tag_image_sdk` when registry_url provided\n- [ ] Add unit tests for `_docker_login_sdk` with mock client\n- [ ] Add unit tests for `_tag_image_sdk` with mock client\n- [ ] Add unit tests for `_get_image_info` edge cases\n- [ ] Verify existing tests still pass\n- [ ] Run `pytest tests/test_docker_service.py` to validate\n\n---\n\n## 7. References\n\n- Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Requirement: Docker integration (lines 135-151)\n- Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md` — DockerService class signature\n- AR-021 — CLI build command (uses DockerService)\n- AR-022 — CLI publish command (uses DockerService)\n- Docker SDK for Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775875678233,"end":1775875678261}}}}
